  "final_text": "I need the ELF path before I can run the recipe. Let me search for it.\n`uart_buf_count` sounds like a VCP/UART variable \u2014 the **VCP-ECHO** project is the most likely match. Running the check:\nThe gdbserver failed to enumerate any ST-LINK probe \u2014 the board isn't being detected. The full error from the server:\n\n```\nST-Link enumeration failed\nError in initializing ST-LINK device.\nReason: ST-LINK DLL error.\n```\n\n**What to check:**\n\n1. **USB connection** \u2014 make sure the NUCLEO-L476RG is plugged in via its ST-LINK USB port (CN1, labelled \"USB ST-LINK\"), not the user USB port.\n2. **ST-LINK firmware** \u2014 your bench F401RE has a known `DEV_USB_COMM_ERR` with V2J28M17 firmware pending upgrade. If this is the same cable/hub path, that could be the root cause. Run ST-LINK Upgrade in STM32CubeProgrammer to bring the onboard ST-LINK to V2J45 or later.\n3. **Confirm probe is visible** \u2014 run `stm32 prog list-probes` to see whether the substrate can enumerate any connected probes right now.\n\nOnce the probe is detected, re-run the same check and it will break at `main`, read `uart_buf_count`, and confirm it equals `0`."
}